Sobukwe was the founder and first president of the PAC. He died at the Kimberley General Hospital on February 27 in 1978. Sobukwe died of lung complications after he was hospitalised in 1977.Â 

His medical doctors requested that he be granted freedom of movement on humanitarian grounds, as he was banished to Galeshewe Township in Kimberley, but it was turned down by the authorities.

